{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":713,"text":"That's how we traveled in the year 1900."},{"time":3422,"text":"That's an open buggy. It doesn't have heating."},{"time":5791,"text":"It doesn't have air conditioning."},{"time":7420,"text":"That horse is pulling it along"},{"time":9477,"text":"at one percent of the speed of sound,"},{"time":11775,"text":"and the rutted dirt road"},{"time":13527,"text":"turns into a quagmire of mud anytime it rains."},{"time":17909,"text":"That's a Boeing 707."},{"time":20654,"text":"Only 60 years later, it travels"},{"time":22955,"text":"at 80 percent of the speed of sound,"},{"time":25172,"text":"and we don't travel any faster today"},{"time":27805,"text":"because commercial supersonic air travel"},{"time":30944,"text":"turned out to be a bust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32913,"text":"So I started wondering and pondering,"},{"time":35465,"text":"could it be that the best years of American economic growth"},{"time":38487,"text":"are behind us?"},{"time":40146,"text":"And that leads to the suggestion, maybe economic growth"},{"time":44625,"text":"is almost over."},{"time":46852,"text":"Some of the reasons for this are not really very controversial."},{"time":50614,"text":"There are four headwinds that are just hitting"},{"time":52988,"text":"the American economy in the face."},{"time":55373,"text":"They're demographics, education, debt and inequality."},{"time":60031,"text":"They're powerful enough to cut growth in half."},{"time":63664,"text":"So we need a lot of innovation to offset this decline."},{"time":68322,"text":"And here's my theme: Because of the headwinds,"},{"time":71090,"text":"if innovation continues to be as powerful as it has been"},{"time":73771,"text":"in the last 150 years, growth is cut in half."},{"time":77638,"text":"If innovation is less powerful,"},{"time":80349,"text":"invents less great, wonderful things,"},{"time":82803,"text":"then growth is going to be even lower than half of history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86813,"text":"Now here's eight centuries of economic growth."},{"time":89968,"text":"The vertical axis is just percent per year of growth,"},{"time":93632,"text":"zero percent a year, one percent a year, two percent a year."},{"time":96755,"text":"The white line is for the U.K., and then the U.S."},{"time":99655,"text":"takes over as the leading nation in the year 1900,"},{"time":102186,"text":"when the line switches to red."},{"time":103677,"text":"You'll notice that, for the first four centuries,"},{"time":105663,"text":"there's hardly any growth at all, just 0.2 percent."},{"time":109533,"text":"Then growth gets better and better."},{"time":111152,"text":"It maxes out in the 1930s, '40s and '50s,"},{"time":114130,"text":"and then it starts slowing down, and here's a cautionary note."},{"time":117887,"text":"That last downward notch in the red line"},{"time":120383,"text":"is not actual data."},{"time":122614,"text":"That is a forecast that I made six years ago"},{"time":125754,"text":"that growth would slow down to 1.3 percent."},{"time":128383,"text":"But you know what the actual facts are?"},{"time":130393,"text":"You know what the growth in per-person income has been"},{"time":132206,"text":"in the United States in the last six years?"},{"time":135098,"text":"Negative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137438,"text":"This led to a fantasy."},{"time":139709,"text":"What if I try to fit a curved line to this historical record?"},{"time":144955,"text":"I can make the curved line end anywhere I wanted,"},{"time":148923,"text":"but I decided I would end it at 0.2,"},{"time":151717,"text":"just like the U.K. growth for the first four centuries."},{"time":156542,"text":"Now the history that we've achieved is that we've grown"},{"time":159906,"text":"at 2.0 percent per year over the whole period,"},{"time":163967,"text":"1891 to 2007,"},{"time":167155,"text":"and remember it's been a little bit negative since 2007."},{"time":170779,"text":"But if growth slows down,"},{"time":173084,"text":"instead of doubling our standard of living every generation,"},{"time":177067,"text":"Americans in the future can't expect to be twice as well off as their parents,"},{"time":181905,"text":"or even a quarter [more well off than] their parents."},{"time":184875,"text":"Now we're going to change and look at the level of per capita income."},{"time":189240,"text":"The vertical axis now is thousands of dollars in today's prices."},{"time":192604,"text":"You'll notice that in 1891, over on the left,"},{"time":195180,"text":"we were at about 5,000 dollars."},{"time":196910,"text":"Today we're at about 44,000 dollars of total output"},{"time":199815,"text":"per member of the population."},{"time":202482,"text":"Now what if we could achieve that historic"},{"time":204900,"text":"two-percent growth for the next 70 years?"},{"time":207883,"text":"Well, it's a matter of arithmetic."},{"time":209215,"text":"Two-percent growth quadruples your standard of living in 70 years."},{"time":213355,"text":"That means we'd go from 44,000 to 180,000."},{"time":217056,"text":"Well, we're not going to do that,"},{"time":219507,"text":"and the reason is the headwinds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221333,"text":"The first headwind is demographics."},{"time":222974,"text":"It's a truism that your standard of living"},{"time":225312,"text":"rises faster than productivity, rises faster than output per hour,"},{"time":228824,"text":"if hours per person increased."},{"time":231434,"text":"And we got that gift back in the '70s and '80s"},{"time":233936,"text":"when women entered the labor force."},{"time":236454,"text":"But now it's turned around."},{"time":238691,"text":"Now hours per person are shrinking,"},{"time":240891,"text":"first because of the retirement of the baby boomers,"},{"time":243765,"text":"and second because there's been a very significant"},{"time":247919,"text":"dropping out of the labor force of prime age adult males"},{"time":251916,"text":"who are in the bottom half of the educational distribution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255854,"text":"The next headwind is education."},{"time":258015,"text":"We've got problems all over our educational system"},{"time":260660,"text":"despite Race to the Top."},{"time":262181,"text":"In college, we've got cost inflation in higher education"},{"time":266263,"text":"that dwarfs cost inflation in medical care."},{"time":269175,"text":"We have in higher education a trillion dollars of student debt,"},{"time":273431,"text":"and our college completion rate"},{"time":276418,"text":"is 15 points, 15 percentage points below Canada."},{"time":283369,"text":"We have a lot of debt."},{"time":285476,"text":"Our economy grew from 2000 to 2007"},{"time":290458,"text":"on the back of consumers massively overborrowing."},{"time":293690,"text":"Consumers paying off that debt is one of the main reasons"},{"time":296626,"text":"why our economic recovery is so sluggish today."},{"time":299362,"text":"And everybody of course knows"},{"time":300948,"text":"that the federal government debt is growing"},{"time":303077,"text":"as a share of GDP at a very rapid rate,"},{"time":306406,"text":"and the only way that's going to stop is some combination"},{"time":309568,"text":"of faster growth in taxes or slower growth in entitlements,"},{"time":314645,"text":"also called transfer payments."},{"time":316730,"text":"And that gets us down from the 1.5,"},{"time":318899,"text":"where we've reached for education, down to 1.3."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322300,"text":"And then we have inequality."},{"time":324718,"text":"Over the 15 years before the financial crisis,"},{"time":327471,"text":"the growth rate of the bottom 99 percent"},{"time":330737,"text":"of the income distribution was half a point slower"},{"time":333860,"text":"than the averages we've been talking about before."},{"time":336636,"text":"All the rest went to the top one percent."},{"time":338922,"text":"So that brings us down to 0.8."},{"time":341274,"text":"And that 0.8 is the big challenge."},{"time":344649,"text":"Are we going to grow at 0.8?"},{"time":346863,"text":"If so, that's going to require that our inventions"},{"time":349318,"text":"are as important as the ones that happened"},{"time":351665,"text":"over the last 150 years."},{"time":354583,"text":"So let's see what some of those inventions were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358622,"text":"If you wanted to read in 1875 at night,"},{"time":362124,"text":"you needed to have an oil or a gas lamp."},{"time":365446,"text":"They created pollution, they created odors,"},{"time":367603,"text":"they were hard to control, the light was dim,"},{"time":370008,"text":"and they were a fire hazard."},{"time":372156,"text":"By 1929, electric light was everywhere."},{"time":377251,"text":"We had the vertical city, the invention of the elevator."},{"time":381400,"text":"Central Manhattan became possible."},{"time":384385,"text":"And then, in addition to that, at the same time,"},{"time":387632,"text":"hand tools were replaced by massive electric tools"},{"time":391128,"text":"and hand-powered electric tools,"},{"time":393836,"text":"all achieved by electricity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396694,"text":"Electricity was also very helpful in liberating women."},{"time":400907,"text":"Women, back in the late 19th century,"},{"time":403595,"text":"spent two days a week doing the laundry."},{"time":406251,"text":"They did it on a scrub board."},{"time":407966,"text":"Then they had to hang the clothes out to dry."},{"time":410034,"text":"Then they had to bring them in."},{"time":411566,"text":"The whole thing took two days out of the seven-day week."},{"time":414519,"text":"And then we had the electric washing machine."},{"time":418106,"text":"And by 1950, they were everywhere."},{"time":421180,"text":"But the women still had to shop every day,"},{"time":424208,"text":"but no they didn't, because electricity"},{"time":426500,"text":"brought us the electric refrigerator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429401,"text":"Back in the late 19th century, the only source of heat in most homes"},{"time":432593,"text":"was a big fireplace in the kitchen that was used for cooking and heating."},{"time":437122,"text":"The bedrooms were cold. They were unheated."},{"time":439438,"text":"But by 1929, certainly by 1950,"},{"time":442118,"text":"we had central heating everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446010,"text":"What about the internal combustion engine,"},{"time":448602,"text":"which was invented in 1879?"},{"time":450942,"text":"In America, before the motor vehicle,"},{"time":454760,"text":"transportation depended entirely on the urban horse,"},{"time":458732,"text":"which dropped, without restraint,"},{"time":461618,"text":"25 to 50 pounds of manure on the streets every day"},{"time":465423,"text":"together with a gallon of urine."},{"time":467347,"text":"That comes out at five to 10 tons daily"},{"time":470560,"text":"per square mile in cities."},{"time":472993,"text":"Those horses also ate up fully one quarter of American agricultural land."},{"time":478934,"text":"That's the percentage of American agricultural land"},{"time":481332,"text":"it took to feed the horses."},{"time":483525,"text":"Of course, when the motor vehicle was invented,"},{"time":487487,"text":"and it became almost ubiquitous by 1929,"},{"time":490691,"text":"that agricultural land could be used for human consumption"},{"time":493786,"text":"or for export."},{"time":495320,"text":"And here's an interesting ratio: Starting from zero in 1900,"},{"time":498960,"text":"only 30 years later, the ratio of motor vehicles to the number of households"},{"time":503876,"text":"in the United States reached 90 percent in just 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510460,"text":"Back before the turn of the century,"},{"time":513271,"text":"women had another problem."},{"time":514672,"text":"All the water for cooking, cleaning and bathing"},{"time":519267,"text":"had to be carried in buckets and pails in from the outside."},{"time":523937,"text":"It's a historical fact that in 1885,"},{"time":526412,"text":"the average North Carolina housewife"},{"time":528726,"text":"walked 148 miles a year carrying 35 tons of water."},{"time":534096,"text":"But by 1929, cities around the country"},{"time":538500,"text":"had put in underground water pipes."},{"time":541515,"text":"They had put in underground sewer pipes,"},{"time":544941,"text":"and as a result, one of the great scourges of the late 19th century,"},{"time":550123,"text":"waterborne diseases like cholera, began to disappear."},{"time":554369,"text":"And an amazing fact for techno-optimists"},{"time":557971,"text":"is that in the first half of the 20th century,"},{"time":560543,"text":"the rate of improvement of life expectancy"},{"time":563255,"text":"was three times faster than it was"},{"time":566056,"text":"in the second half of the 19th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568927,"text":"So it's a truism that things can't be more than 100 percent of themselves."},{"time":574013,"text":"And I'll just give you a few examples."},{"time":576195,"text":"We went from one percent to 90 percent of the speed of sound."},{"time":579463,"text":"Electrification, central heat, ownership of motor cars,"},{"time":583071,"text":"they all went from zero to 100 percent."},{"time":585434,"text":"Urban environments make people more productive than on the farm."},{"time":589084,"text":"We went from 25 percent urban to 75 percent"},{"time":591926,"text":"by the early postwar years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596054,"text":"What about the electronic revolution?"},{"time":598297,"text":"Here's an early computer."},{"time":600418,"text":"It's amazing. The mainframe computer was invented in 1942."},{"time":603728,"text":"By 1960 we had telephone bills, bank statements"},{"time":608281,"text":"were being produced by computers."},{"time":610052,"text":"The earliest cell phones, the earliest personal computers"},{"time":612916,"text":"were invented in the 1970s."},{"time":615831,"text":"The 1980s brought us Bill Gates, DOS,"},{"time":619086,"text":"ATM machines to replace bank tellers,"},{"time":621871,"text":"bar code scanning to cut down on labor in the retail sector."},{"time":625764,"text":"Fast forward through the '90s,"},{"time":627631,"text":"we had the dotcom revolution"},{"time":629199,"text":"and a temporary rise in productivity growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632323,"text":"But I'm now going to give you an experiment."},{"time":634775,"text":"You have to choose either option A or option B."},{"time":637863,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":640378,"text":"Option A is you get to keep everything invented up till 10 years ago."},{"time":643719,"text":"So you get Google, you get Amazon,"},{"time":646629,"text":"you get Wikipedia, and you get running water and indoor toilets."},{"time":649716,"text":"Or you get everything invented to yesterday,"},{"time":651545,"text":"including Facebook and your iPhone,"},{"time":653621,"text":"but you have to give up, go out to the outhouse,"},{"time":655980,"text":"and carry in the water."},{"time":658844,"text":"Hurricane Sandy caused a lot of people to lose the 20th century,"},{"time":662294,"text":"maybe for a couple of days,"},{"time":663817,"text":"in some cases for more than a week,"},{"time":665943,"text":"electricity, running water, heating, gasoline for their cars,"},{"time":669483,"text":"and a charge for their iPhones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672399,"text":"The problem we face is that all these great inventions,"},{"time":675910,"text":"we have to match them in the future,"},{"time":678914,"text":"and my prediction that we're not going to match them"},{"time":681502,"text":"brings us down from the original two-percent growth"},{"time":684697,"text":"down to 0.2, the fanciful curve that I drew you at the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689767,"text":"So here we are back to the horse and buggy."},{"time":692774,"text":"I'd like to award an Oscar"},{"time":695095,"text":"to the inventors of the 20th century,"},{"time":698748,"text":"the people from Alexander Graham Bell"},{"time":701489,"text":"to Thomas Edison to the Wright Brothers,"},{"time":703192,"text":"I'd like to call them all up here,"},{"time":704915,"text":"and they're going to call back to you."},{"time":706785,"text":"Your challenge is, can you match what we achieved?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":710448,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711982,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}